      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING GRINCH (5) was well fancied last time on the back of some sparkling form, which included a two-start winning streak, but could only manage fourth (30.00) at Wentworth Park. Key runner on his best form. SKETCHY STORY (2) jumped well and was in the mix early before fading out of it late when 7th over 520m at Wentworth Park in Grade 4/5 company. Expected to feature in the finish. LORD EDDIE (7) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.5 lengths at this track in a handy 22.44 beating MAGIC LINKIN. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Expected to feature again. MAGIC LINKIN (4) is a last-start placegetter with solid claims again.",
